cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "F(AI²)R: FAIR research with AI in the loop, twice"
message: "If you use this work, please cite it as below."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: "TBD"
    given-names: "TBD"
    affiliation: "TBD"
abstract: >-
  F(AI²)R extends the FAIR principles (Findable, Accessible, Interoperable,
  Reusable) for scholarly artefacts produced with the active participation of
  Large Language Models. AI participates twice — as assistant in authoring and
  as auditor of provenance — and both passes are captured in a PROV-O graph
  that travels with the manuscript.
keywords:
  - FAIR
  - PROV-O
  - reproducibility
  - LLM
  - scholarly communication
  - provenance
license: MIT
